from the refrigerator and the cupboard,

29:16.365 --> 29:17.615
- and put it in here.
- What's going on?

29:17.700 --> 29:19.701
- Just tell me.
- Just do it.

29:20.160 --> 29:22.620
- Rachel, sweetheart...
- Dad, you're really scaring me.

29:22.705 --> 29:25.123
...I need you to get your suitcase...
- Dad.

29:25.207 --> 29:27.792
...the one that you brought,
bring it to me, okay?

29:27.876 --> 29:31.004
Can you just do that for me, darling?
Okay?

29:45.894 --> 29:47.520
I don't think it's a fire.

29:48.480 --> 29:51.941
- See? That looks like smoke to me.
- What's happening?

29:52.026 --> 29:55.987
I can't tell you now.
We've only got about another minute.

30:02.161 --> 30:05.580
Please.

30:11.712 --> 30:14.005
- Just keep it down.
- Ray, I'm standing right beside you.

30:14.089 --> 30:16.299
Can you please answer me?

30:17.885 --> 30:20.386
Just get in the front seat, Robbie.

30:25.184 --> 30:26.684
- Whose car is this?
- Just get in.

30:26.769 --> 30:28.603
Whose car is this?

30:31.273 --> 30:33.858
Hey. Hey, Ray.
You were absolutely right.

30:33.942 --> 30:36.486
That is exact... I had to change the...

30:37.613 --> 30:39.614
Ray? Hey.

30:39.698 --> 30:42.075
Hey, Ray? Ray.

30:43.118 --> 30:44.619
Ray.

30:45.621 --> 30:49.082
What? Come on, open up.
Open the door, come on.

30:49.166 --> 30:52.001
- Open the door, Ray. What are you...
- Get in, Manny.

30:52.086 --> 30:53.336
That's funny.
You got to get out of the car.

30:53.420 --> 30:55.213
- Manny, get in the car.
- It's not my car. It's not your car.

30:55.297 --> 30:56.380
Manny, listen to me, pal.

30:56.465 --> 30:58.216
- Manny, Manny, shut up.
- Kids, Daddy's acting crazy.

30:58.300 --> 31:00.218
You can't do this. Guy's gonna
come back, he's not gonna...

31:00.302 --> 31:01.928
Manny. Manny,
I don't have time to explain.

31:02.012 --> 31:03.554
You're busting my chops.
I got a shop to run.

31:03.639 --> 31:05.098
- Manny, listen to me.
- No, Ray. Get out of the...

31:05.182 --> 31:07.683
Get in, Manny, or you're gonna die.

31:07.768 --> 31:09.519
- What do you mean?
- Okay.

31:11.146 --> 31:12.647
All right, get out of the truck.
I'm not kidding now.

31:12.731 --> 31:14.482
Get out of the car, Ray.

31:14.566 --> 31:16.400
I'm not gonna get in. I'm not getting in.

31:16.485 --> 31:19.237
- Manny, get in with us.
- I'm not gonna get in trouble.

31:19.321 --> 31:22.657
- Look, I'm not fooling around...
- Close the door. Close it.

31:23.450 --> 31:27.078
Ray, bring the car back, Ray.
It's not my car.

31:31.917 --> 31:34.418
Get down! Get down, get down!
Get down!

31:34.503 --> 31:35.753
Is it the terrorists?

31:35.838 --> 31:38.798
- Just get down. Get down! Get down!
- Holy shit!

32:10.956 --> 32:13.124
- Where are we going?
- We got to go.

32:13.208 --> 32:15.126
We got, maybe, like,
the only working car around here.

32:15.210 --> 32:18.296
- I'm not stopping until we're clear of it.
- Clear of what?

32:18.380 --> 32:19.797
- We got to go.
- What the hell is going on?

32:19.882 --> 32:22.383
- Look, you saw, we're under attack!
- By who?

32:22.467 --> 32:23.801
Who is attacking us?

32:23.886 --> 32:26.679
Rachel?
Rachel, you've got to keep it down.

32:26.763 --> 32:28.806
Rachel. Rachel. Shut up, Rachel.

32:28.891 --> 32:32.977
- You're freaking her out!
- Look, I'm driving! Do something!

32:33.061 --> 32:35.479
Okay, put them up, Rach.
Make the arms.

32:35.564 --> 32:38.399
This space right here, this is yours.
This belongs to you, right?

32:38.483 --> 32:39.901
- Yes.
- You're safe in your space.

32:39.985 --> 32:41.444
- I'm safe in my space.
- You're safe in your space.

32:41.528 --> 32:43.154
Nothing can happen to you
in your space.

32:43.238 --> 32:44.280
- Okay.
- I'm really scared.

32:44.364 --> 32:45.865
I'm gonna go to the front seat,
I'm gonna talk to Dad.

32:45.949 --> 32:47.241
- No.
- I'll be two feet away. Okay?

32:47.326 --> 32:48.826
- Okay.
- Will you hold my hand?

32:48.911 --> 32:50.036
- Will you hold my hand?
- Yes.

32:50.120 --> 32:51.954
- Are you gonna be okay?
- Yes.

32:53.957 --> 32:56.125
I wanna know everything you know.

32:56.960 --> 32:58.336
This...

32:58.420 --> 33:00.296
This thing, this machine,
it crawled out of the ground,

33:00.380 --> 33:03.841
started torching everything.
It was killing everybody.

33:03.926 --> 33:06.636
What is it? Is it terrorists?

33:06.720 --> 33:09.513
No, this came from someplace else.

33:09.598 --> 33:13.392
- What do you mean, like Europe?
- No, Robbie, not like Europe!

33:23.695 --> 33:28.157
That machine, it was already buried.

33:29.284 --> 33:31.410
Maybe it...

33:31.495 --> 33:34.622
It came down in the lightning storm.

33:35.290 --> 33:38.709
- They came down in the lightning storm.
- What do you mean "came down"?

33:38.794 --> 33:41.754
- You just said it was buried.
- No, the machine I'm talking about

33:41.838 --> 33:45.967
was buried, but what came down
in the lightning storm,

33:46.051 --> 33:50.554
what operates it, that's the... You know.

33:50.639 --> 33:52.014
- The what?
- That's the...

33:52.099 --> 33:54.642
Why aren't there any helicopters
or airplanes?

33:54.726 --> 33:57.395
- It's the what?
- Hey, Rach. How you doing there, girl?

33:57.479 --> 33:58.813
- How is she doing?
- How you doing?

33:58.897 --> 34:00.022
- Fine.
- She's good.

34:00.107 --> 34:02.483
Yeah? Good.
What was that thing you did with her?

34:02.567 --> 34:03.776
Works sometimes.
She gets claustrophobic.

34:03.860 --> 34:05.278
Yeah? Hey, Rachel? Hey.

34:05.362 --> 34:07.238
- I want Mom.
- Yeah, I know. You feel better?

34:07.322 --> 34:10.533
- I want Mom.
- Yeah? Tell me about it, you know?

34:10.617 --> 34:12.034
- Take me to Mom's.
- Listen, what I need you to do is,

34:12.119 --> 34:14.370
is I just need you to hold it together
for me, okay?

34:14.454 --> 34:15.705
I want Mom!

34:15.789 --> 34:18.081
When you start screaming like that,
you know, I can't really drive...

34:18.166 --> 34:19.667
- Take me to Mom's!
- I know that.

34:19.751 --> 34:21.252
That's where we're going right now.

34:21.335 --> 34:22.670
- Rachel...
- Take me to Mom's!

34:22.754 --> 34:24.338
I know!

34:40.147 --> 34:42.188
Hurry up, Dad. Come on.

34:49.197 --> 34:51.114
Robbie, get the door.

34:53.034 --> 34:54.618
Mom!

34:54.703 --> 34:56.454
- Mom!
- Mom!

34:56.538 --> 34:58.372
Mom!

34:59.041 --> 35:06.547
Mom? Tim?

35:10.010 --> 35:11.719
- Mom?
- Mom?

35:11.803 --> 35:14.472
- Tim?
- Tim?

35:16.183 --> 35:17.892
Tim?

35:18.727 --> 35:19.894
Mom?

35:22.022 --> 35:23.564
They're gone.

35:23.648 --> 35:25.775
Is she dead?

35:25.859 --> 35:27.693
She's not dead. All right?

35:27.778 --> 35:29.445
She's just not here, okay?

35:29.529 --> 35:31.906
- They were never here.
- How do you know?

35:31.990 --> 35:34.241
Because they're on their way to Boston.

35:34.326 --> 35:37.370
And so they just
kept on going up to Boston.

35:37.454 --> 35:39.163
They're probably
at your grandma's house by now.

35:39.247 --> 35:40.498
I'm gonna call her.

35:40.582 --> 35:43.459
How come the lights are on here
and not at your place?

35:43.543 --> 35:46.504
Because nothing bad happened here.
Okay?

35:46.588 --> 35:48.923
So we're safe here. All right?

35:49.007 --> 35:51.175
Okay, Rachel? This is your area.

35:51.259 --> 35:54.637
- Okay, you are safe...
- Dad, that's not how it goes.

35:54.721 --> 35:57.515
Okay. Well, are you hungry?
I'll get you some food.

35:57.599 --> 36:00.768
I'm gonna feed you.
Get something to eat.

36:00.852 --> 36:02.103
- What do we have? We have...
- Busy signal.

36:02.187 --> 36:04.021
- It's one of the fast ones.
- What is this? Ketchup, mustard...

36:04.106 --> 36:07.233
- You think all the circuits are down?
- Tabasco, barbecue sauce.

36:07.317 --> 36:10.027
You know, this is really good, Robbie.
Vinaigrette. I said pack food.

36:10.112 --> 36:13.197
- What the hell is this?
- That's all that was in your kitchen.

36:13.281 --> 36:15.908
Okay. That's all right.

36:16.910 --> 36:19.036
All right. Okay.

36:22.457 --> 36:24.542
Food. Bread.

36:25.627 --> 36:28.129
Okay. We're gonna have...

36:29.339 --> 36:31.132
Let's get some sandwiches.

36:33.844 --> 36:35.428
Wanna see me deal?

36:36.138 --> 36:37.972
Wanna see me deal? Here we go.

36:38.056 --> 36:40.683
There's two for you.
There's two for Robbie.

36:40.767 --> 36:42.852
There's two for me, one for the house.

36:46.148 --> 36:47.565
Okay.

36:47.649 --> 36:50.484
Maybe after we eat something,
I'll go down and show you guys...

36:50.569 --> 36:53.404
Teach you how to play some poker?
A little five-card stud?

36:53.488 --> 36:56.615
- Maybe a little blackjack.
- I'm allergic to peanut butter.

36:57.409 --> 36:59.118
Since when?

36:59.202 --> 37:00.494
Birth.

37:04.207 --> 37:05.958
Okay, well, here.

37:06.042 --> 37:08.085
You can eat the bread. Okay?

37:08.170 --> 37:09.628
I'm not hungry.

37:11.173 --> 37:12.923
Okay, well,

37:13.008 --> 37:15.342
Robbie and I are gonna be eating
peanut butter sandwiches.

37:15.427 --> 37:18.512
- Want jelly on this sandwich?
- I'm not hungry either.

37:18.597 --> 37:21.891
You're not hungry either? Okay.

37:21.975 --> 37:24.268
Okay, that's fine.

37:33.153 --> 37:35.362
Everybody just relax, okay?

37:35.447 --> 37:38.949
Because we're here now.
We're safe, and we're gonna stay.

37:39.034 --> 37:41.243
And in the morning,
your mom and Tim are gonna be here.

37:41.328 --> 37:42.953
And everything's gonna be fine.

37:43.038 --> 37:44.497
Okay?

37:45.957 --> 37:47.374
Okay.

37:51.379 --> 37:53.881
If everything's fine, why do we
have to sleep in the basement?

37:53.965 --> 37:57.301
- We've got perfectly good beds.
- Hey, it's like a slumber party.

37:57.385 --> 37:58.886
What are you afraid
is gonna happen to us?

37:58.970 --> 38:00.554
Nice basement.

38:00.639 --> 38:03.891
I wanna sleep in my bed.
I've got back problems.

38:05.644 --> 38:07.269
Okay. Well...

38:07.354 --> 38:09.980
You know on the weather channel
when there's a tornado,

38:10.065 --> 38:12.691
and they tell you to go down
to the basement for safety? It's like that.

38:12.776 --> 38:14.818
- There's gonna be tornadoes?
- Okay, Rachel.

38:14.903 --> 38:17.530
Hey, no more talking, okay?

38:17.614 --> 38:19.573
- Could you be a little nicer to me?
- No more talking.

38:19.658 --> 38:20.950
God.

38:25.830 --> 38:26.914
- Wanna stay here?
- Yeah.

38:26.998 --> 38:28.582
- Good.
- Good night. Love you.

38:28.667 --> 38:30.417
Love you, Rach.

39:44.868 --> 39:46.827
Is the lightning back?

39:48.163 --> 39:50.331
No, this is something else.

40:10.018 --> 40:12.603
- What's that sound?
- I've never heard that before!

40:12.687 --> 40:14.104
Is it them? Is it them?

40:16.149 --> 40:17.358
We got to go.

40:17.442 --> 40:19.318
Where do we go?
Robbie, this is your house.

40:19.402 --> 40:20.944
Where do we go?

40:31.998 --> 40:33.624
No, no, no, wait!

40:52.644 --> 40:55.104
Are we still alive?

42:47.801 --> 42:49.551
Down here.

42:53.807 --> 42:55.766
Were you on this plane?

42:56.976 --> 42:59.228
Are you... Are you a passenger?

43:06.152 --> 43:09.071
How you doing?
Wanna help me open this?

43:11.574 --> 43:13.450
Are you a passenger?

43:13.535 --> 43:15.327
He's deaf.

43:15.411 --> 43:19.122
The shell went off right beside him.
Camera on his shoulder saved his life.

43:19.207 --> 43:20.666
You hear that, Max?

43:20.750 --> 43:23.544
Your stupid camera
saved your stupid life.

43:24.212 --> 43:26.046
Where were you?

43:26.548 --> 43:29.258
Out there in the Pine Barrens.

43:29.342 --> 43:31.301
We were attached to
a National Guard unit.

43:31.386 --> 43:32.970
The 83rd Mechanized.

43:33.054 --> 43:35.347
They moved on one of those things
around midnight.

43:35.431 --> 43:37.140
They've got some kind of shield
around them.

43:37.225 --> 43:39.977
You can't see it, but everything
we fire at them detonates too early,

43:40.061 --> 43:43.313
before we can get close enough
to cause any damage.

43:43.398 --> 43:47.192
When they flash that thing,
everything lights up like Hiroshima.

43:47.861 --> 43:50.070
There's more than one?

43:51.155 --> 43:52.823
You got to be kidding me, right?

43:54.284 --> 43:56.493
We were feeding New York,
but New York went dark.

43:56.578 --> 43:59.037
So we patched over to DC,
they went down.

43:59.122 --> 44:01.957
LA, Chicago, uplinked to London.

44:02.041 --> 44:05.294
Even called the affiliates
to try to get them to catch the feed,

44:05.378 --> 44:08.213
but nobody answers.
It's the same everywhere.

44:08.298 --> 44:12.217
Once the Tripods start to move,
no more news comes out of that area.

44:23.271 --> 44:25.022
My God.

44:26.107 --> 44:28.066
You ain't seen nothing yet.

44:30.904 --> 44:34.197
I saw that storm.
I was right in the middle of one of those.

44:34.282 --> 44:35.991
Well, you didn't see it like this.

44:36.075 --> 44:38.535
Those machines come up
from under the ground, right?

44:38.620 --> 44:41.622
So that means they must've been
buried here a long time ago.

44:41.706 --> 44:45.918
So who's driving the goddamn things?
Watch the lightning.

44:46.002 --> 44:47.711
Watch it.

44:49.130 --> 44:50.589
Watch the lightning.

44:50.673 --> 44:52.925
Keep watching the lightning.

44:56.638 --> 44:58.639
What is that?

44:58.806 --> 45:03.060
That is them.
They come down in capsules,

45:03.144 --> 45:06.104
riding the lightning into the ground,
into the machines, right?

45:09.067 --> 45:11.068
You hear that?

45:11.152 --> 45:13.570
We're getting the hell out of here.

45:16.991 --> 45:18.742
Get in, get in, get in, get in.

45:20.328 --> 45:23.413
Hey, were you on that plane?

45:25.458 --> 45:28.794
That's too bad.
It would've been a really great story.

45:30.505 --> 45:32.673
Look at me. Look at me.

45:32.840 --> 45:35.092
You keep your eyes only on me,
understand?

45:35.176 --> 45:37.135
- Okay.
- Don't look down. Don't look around me.

45:37.845 --> 45:40.973
I'm taking you to the car.
You're gonna want to look around.

45:41.057 --> 45:42.766
But you're not going to.

45:42.850 --> 45:44.393
- Are you?
- No.

45:44.686 --> 45:48.188
You're doing good. You're doing good.
Keep your eyes on me.

45:48.272 --> 45:49.564
I'm going right to Boston.

45:49.649 --> 45:51.984
- We're gonna see your mom.
- I'm not gonna look, Dad.

45:52.068 --> 45:54.152
That's a girl. That's my girl. Now listen.

45:54.237 --> 45:56.071
- I want you to close your eyes, okay?
- Okay.

45:56.155 --> 45:58.615
Got them closed? There you go.

45:58.700 --> 46:01.034
- Keep them closed for me.
- Okay.

46:06.332 --> 46:07.874
Robbie, get in.

46:09.585 --> 46:11.378
- Robbie, get in!
- Why are you yelling?

46:11.462 --> 46:12.963
It's okay.

46:15.550 --> 46:17.050
Get in.

46:37.530 --> 46:40.032
- Why the hell aren't we on the turnpike?
- Because I don't want everybody

46:40.116 --> 46:42.659
to see that we've got a working car.
We'll stay along the Hudson

46:42.744 --> 46:46.079
till we find an open bridge or ferry,
then we're gonna cross the Hudson.

46:46.164 --> 46:50.417
We'll take the back roads across
Connecticut, all the way to Boston.

46:50.501 --> 46:53.420
- Where is everybody?
- I don't know, running, hiding.

46:53.504 --> 46:55.714
- Hiding in their basements.
- lf we had any balls, we'd go back there

46:55.798 --> 46:59.468
- and find one of those things and kill it.
- Right. Yeah, good.

46:59.552 --> 47:01.636
Why don't you just let me
make the big decisions, okay?

47:01.721 --> 47:03.305
Which would be when? Never, Ray?

47:03.389 --> 47:04.848
- Never's about your speed.
- Stop it, Robbie.

47:04.932 --> 47:06.975
Enough of the "Ray" shit. All right?

47:07.060 --> 47:08.477
- It's "Dad," "sir"...
- Don't fight!

47:08.561 --> 47:10.687
...or if you want, "Mr. Ferrier."

47:10.772 --> 47:14.066
That sounds a little weird to me,
but you decide.

47:14.609 --> 47:17.444
- Dad?
- Yes, Rachel.

47:19.739 --> 47:22.032
I've got to go to the bathroom.

47:22.867 --> 47:24.451
Really?

47:30.958 --> 47:33.293
- I got to go.
- Not so fast, not so fast, all right?

47:33.377 --> 47:35.337
There's two things
we got to watch out for.

47:35.421 --> 47:38.006
And the second is people
who might want our car.

47:38.091 --> 47:40.842
- There's nobody around.
- Yeah. I got to go.

47:48.518 --> 47:51.353
All right. Rachel?
Rachel, it's good right there.

47:51.437 --> 47:53.730
I'm not going in front of you guys.

47:53.815 --> 47:56.233
All right,
then just go where I can see you.

47:56.317 --> 47:57.818
Are you crazy?

47:57.902 --> 47:59.903
- Don't look!
- Well, I'm not gonna look.

47:59.987 --> 48:02.823
- Just stay in sight!
- That's looking!

48:04.242 --> 48:07.119
Okay, well, listen, every time
you guys don't listen to me,

48:07.203 --> 48:10.497
I'm telling your mother, okay?
I'm making a list.

48:11.999 --> 48:13.708
Making a list.

48:56.002 --> 48:59.462
- I told you to stay where I could see you.
- Sorry. I'm sorry.

49:14.228 --> 49:15.812
Stop! Don't go!

49:15.897 --> 49:18.148
Wait! Stop! Let me on!

49:18.232 --> 49:20.567
Let me on! Give me a hand!

49:20.651 --> 49:22.235
Wait! Stop!

49:22.361 --> 49:24.154
- Stop! Give me a hand!
- Hey, watch it, kid,

49:24.238 --> 49:25.280
you're gonna get yourself run over!

49:25.364 --> 49:28.325
- Give me a hand! You have room!
- Robbie!

49:28.409 --> 49:31.411
- Robbie, you wanna go in that direction?
- Stop! Stop! Wait!

49:31.495 --> 49:34.289
There's nothing living
in that direction, Robbie.

49:34.373 --> 49:36.750
What do you care?
You never gave a shit before.

49:36.834 --> 49:39.085
- You never gave a shit!
- Okay, hard-ass,

49:39.170 --> 49:41.463
what's your plan, huh?
You're in charge now!

49:41.547 --> 49:43.048
You tell me what we're doing.
What do we do?

49:43.132 --> 49:45.508
We catch up with these soldiers!
Hook up with whoever else isn't dead,

49:45.593 --> 49:47.052
and we get back at them.

49:47.136 --> 49:50.597
We get back at them.
That's what we do.

49:50.681 --> 49:55.018
Now let's try one that doesn't involve
your 10-year-old sister joining the Army.

49:55.102 --> 49:57.354
- You have anything like that?
- Why don't you just tell us the truth?

49:57.438 --> 49:59.606
- Wanna try something like that?
- You have no idea which way to go.

49:59.690 --> 50:02.234
- You have anything like that?
- You wanna come off all wise and shit!

50:02.318 --> 50:05.028
You only chose Boston
because you hoped Mom was there.

50:05.112 --> 50:07.530
And if she's there,
you can dump us on her.

50:07.615 --> 50:11.284
You can dump us on her, and then
you'll only have to care about yourself,

50:11.369 --> 50:14.371
which is exactly the way you like it.

50:15.915 --> 50:19.709
Robbie! Where are you trying to go?

50:19.794 --> 50:22.254
What are you trying to do?

50:23.214 --> 50:26.258
Who's gonna take care of me if you go?

50:44.318 --> 50:47.320
This is a test of
the Emergency Alert System.

50:47.655 --> 50:50.365
If this had been an actual emergency,
official messages

50:50.449 --> 50:54.452
from federajl, state or jlocajl authorities
would have followed the alert tone.

50:54.537 --> 50:57.539
This concludes the test
of the Emergency Alert...

50:59.125 --> 51:02.252
I'll close my eyes.
Why don't you drive for a bit?

51:02.920 --> 51:05.005
I don't have a license.

51:06.090 --> 51:08.466
Since when has that stopped you?

51:39.081 --> 51:40.832
Ray.

51:42.835 --> 51:45.170
Ray! Dad!

51:48.799 --> 51:50.342
You think you could...

51:50.426 --> 51:53.136
You think you could...
Do you think you could...

51:53.888 --> 51:55.388
Don't stop.

51:55.473 --> 51:57.640
Don't take your foot off. Okay?

51:57.725 --> 52:00.810
I got it, but keep your foot on.
Okay, I got it. I got it.

52:00.895 --> 52:03.772
- Where is everybody going?
- I don't know, Rach.

52:03.856 --> 52:05.982
But we do, right?

52:06.067 --> 52:07.984
Yeah, we do.

52:19.747 --> 52:21.414
Why did he do that?

52:23.584 --> 52:25.668
- Why is he doing that?
